Sentencas: Porous electrodes based on the system La0.85Sr0.15Cr1-xNixO3-delta (x = 0.1 and 0.2) have been investigated as anodes for proton conducting solid oxide fuel cells based on the La5.6WO11.4-delta (LWO) electrolyte material.
Titulo: Development and understanding of La0.85Sr0.15Cr1-xNixO3-δ anodes for La5.6WO11.4-δ-based Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The microstructure of the anodes was optimized by varying both the starting powder morphology and the final anode sintering temperature.
Titulo: Development and understanding of La0.85Sr0.15Cr1-xNixO3-δ anodes for La5.6WO11.4-δ-based Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Two different electrode thicknesses were studied, i.e. 15 and 30 gm.
Titulo: Development and understanding of La0.85Sr0.15Cr1-xNixO3-δ anodes for La5.6WO11.4-δ-based Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The importance of the catalytic role of Ni was also studied by using different concentrations of Ni (10% and 20%) in the chromite and by tuning the Ni particle sizes through the control of the reduction temperature.
Titulo: Development and understanding of La0.85Sr0.15Cr1-xNixO3-δ anodes for La5.6WO11.4-δ-based Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Additionally, a ceramic-ceramic (cer-cer) composite electrode comprising a physical mixture of the optimized chromite and LWO phase was also considered.
Titulo: Development and understanding of La0.85Sr0.15Cr1-xNixO3-δ anodes for La5.6WO11.4-δ-based Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Finally, a kinetics study and modeling based on Langmuir-Hinshelwood mechanism was carried out in order to quantitatively describe the rate of dissociative adsorption of H-2 on the Ni particles spread on the chromite surface.
Titulo: Development and understanding of La0.85Sr0.15Cr1-xNixO3-δ anodes for La5.6WO11.4-δ-based Proton Conducting Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
